whereas.text:
Whereas at least 79 fugitives from the United States,
			 charged with offenses ranging from hijacking to kidnapping to drug offenses to
			 murder, are believed to be receiving safe harbor in Cuba;

Whereas according to treaties enacted in 1905 and 1926 (33
			 Stat. 2265, 33 Stat. 2273, and 44 Stat. 2392), the United States has a
			 bilateral extradition treaty with Cuba;

Whereas in January 2002, Cuba deported to the United
			 States Jesse James Bell, a United States fugitive wanted on drug
			 charges;
